translated: Ekholm, Einar Andreas, district physician, Nässjö, b. 29/11/97 in Uppsala, to factory worker Anders E. and Elin Matilda Österberg. Married in 1924 to Margareta Kristina Eleonora Abrahamsson. Children: Karin Margareta b. 1927, studying medicine, Anders b. 1932. Einar passed his studentexamen in 1915, followed by a Bachelor of Medicine in 1918 and a Doctor of Medicine in 1923, all at Uppsala University. He received a scholarship for a medical residency at Fik res, 1921-1923, then worked as a naval doctor in Uppsala from 1923-1925, assistant physician and temporary deputy senior physician at Jönköping Hospital from 1923-1924, deputy senior physician there from 1924-1925, senior physician at Västerås Hospital from 1925-1926, temporary senior physician at Jönköping Hospital and Västerås Hospital in 1926, deputy senior physician at Kolmården Sanatorium from 1926-1927, temporary district physician in the Arvidsjaur district in 1927, district physician in the Tärna district, medical director at Tärnaby and medical officer at Tärna-Stensele Dispensary from 1927-1929, assistant physician at Stockholm's epidemic hospital in 1929, district physician in Nässjö district since 1929, medical director and physician at Nässjö samre-alsk. Belongs to the temperance society and the pension society.
